{{出典の明記|date=2017th year 10月14日 (土) 10:04 (UTC)}} '''Rokuyokuten''' (六欲天) refers to the six heavens of the [[:en:Devaloka|Heavenly Realms]] ({{ill|天上界|ja|天上界|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) that remain bound by desires. It is also known as the Six Heavens. Sometimes, it specifically refers to the highest of these heavens, the {{ill|Takijizaiten|ja|他化自在天|qq=draft|qq=draft}}{{efn|Takijizaiten is the dwelling place of the {{ill|Demon King of the Sixth Heaven|ja|天魔波旬|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, and it is said that {{ill|Oda Nobunaga|ja|織田信長|qq=draft|qq=draft}} referred to himself as the "Demon King of the Six Heavens"{{要出典|date=2017th year 10月14日 (土) 10:04 (UTC)|title=}}.}}.
== Overview == In {{ill|Buddhism|ja|仏教|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, the worldview includes the {{ill|Six Realms of Existence|ja|六道|qq=draft|qq=draft}} ({{ill|Hell|ja|地獄界|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Hungry Ghosts|ja|餓鬼界|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Animals|ja|畜生界|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Asuras|ja|修羅界|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Human Realm|ja|人間界|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, and {{ill|Heavenly Realms|ja|天上界|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) and the Ten Realms (adding the {{ill|Realm of Śrāvakas|ja|声聞界|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Realm of Pratyekabuddhas|ja|縁覚界|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Realm of Bodhisattvas|ja|菩薩界|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, and {{ill|Realm of Buddhas|ja|仏界|qq=draft|qq=draft}} to the Six Realms).
Of these, the realms from Hell to the Human Realm are worlds bound by desires, collectively called the {{ill|Desire Realm|ja|欲界|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. However, the Heavenly Realms are divided into finer gradations, where the higher levels gradually detach from desires and ascend to the material {{ill|Form Realm|ja|色界|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and the spiritual {{ill|Formless Realm|ja|無色界|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, collectively referred to as the {{ill|Three Realms|ja|三界|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
Within the Heavenly Realms, the six lower heavens nearest to the Human Realm are still bound by desires and are thus included in the Desire Realm, collectively known as the '''Six Heavens of Desire''' (Rokuyokuten).
The Six Heavens of Desire, listed from highest to lowest, are as follows:
* {{ill|Takijizaiten|ja|他化自在天|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (たけじざいてん) : The highest of the Desire Realm. It is the sixth heaven of the Six Heavens, the dwelling place of {{ill|Demon King of the Sixth Heaven|ja|天魔波旬|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. * {{ill|Keratuten|ja|化楽天|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (けらくてん, also known as 楽変化天) : The fifth heaven. The beings of this realm transform their surroundings into sources of enjoyment. * {{ill|Tosotsuten|ja|兜率天|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (とそつてん, also known as 覩史多天) : The fourth heaven. Located atop {{ill|Mount Sumeru|ja|須弥山|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, 12 {{ill|Yojana|ja|由旬|qq=draft|qq=draft}} high. * {{ill|Yamaten|ja|夜摩天|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (やまてん, also known as 焔摩天) : The third heaven. A realm where beings experience pleasure according to time. * {{ill|Toriten|ja|忉利天|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (とうりてん, also known as 三十三天) : The second heaven. Located at the summit of Mount Sumeru, above Jambudvīpa, 80,000 yojanas high, and the dwelling place of {{ill|Indra|ja|帝釈天|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. * {{ill|Shitenno|ja|四大王衆天|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (しだいおうしゅてん, also known as 四天王衆天) : The first heaven. Home to the {{ill|Four Heavenly Kings|ja|四天王|qq=draft|qq=draft}}: {{ill|Dhṛtarāṣṭra|ja|持国天|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Virūḍhaka|ja|増長天|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Virūpākṣa|ja|広目天|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, and {{ill|Vaiśravaṇa|ja|多聞天|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
